Parliament, Tuesday, 18 May 2021 – The Portfolio Committee on Public Works and Infrastructure will this week conduct public hearings on the Expropriation Bill in KwaZulu-Natal Province.
	
	The district municipalities that will be hosting the public hearings include, Dundee, Ulundi, Richards Bay and KwaXimba.
	
	The committee has successfully conducted public hearings in Limpopo, Mpumalanga, North West and Gauteng province on the Bill.
	
	The KZN leg of the hearings will start on Thursday, 20 May and end on Sunday, 23 May.
	
	Details of Thursday’s programme are as follows:
	
	Date: Thursday, 20 May 2021
	Venue: Endumeni Local Municipality
	Moth War Memorial Hall
	Time: 09h00 – 15h00
	
